Subject: Recommendation on Caching Strategy and Clarification Needed on Unmapped Articles

Hi [Name],

While working on the website resampling, I encountered two important points that require your guidance:

1. Recommendation: Implement Redis Caching Instead of Increasing YouTube API Quota

We recently exceeded the daily YouTube Data API v3 quota (10,000 units/day), which caused related features to stop working. After evaluating options, Redis caching is the more scalable and cost-efficient solution compared to requesting higher API quota.

Benefits of Redis caching:

Reduces API calls drastically (from thousands/day to <100/day)

Keeps us comfortably within the free quota

Improves performance under high footfall

Redis can also be reused to cache many other pages across the site, not just YouTube data

Increasing quota is not guaranteed and could lead to higher backend processing costs as traffic grows.

Therefore, I recommend proceeding with Redis caching.

2. Unmapped Articles That Do Not Appear in Any Frontend Category

During the ingestion pipeline (e.g., /blogs/slug), we discovered many articles/pages that:

Exist in the backend

Are accessible via URLs like https://example.com/slug

